995
01:34:25,080 --> 01:34:27,071
Your turn now.

996
01:34:38,040 --> 01:34:40,634
Oh, that's enough.

997
01:34:40,840 --> 01:34:43,354
Don't forget I'm a little girl.

998
01:34:43,560 --> 01:34:46,597
And, anyway, you know, the main
reason I think it's so lovely...

999
01:34:46,800 --> 01:34:50,190
...is because of the bubbles.
- Well, I am thirsty.

1000
01:34:50,840 --> 01:34:53,195
Pierre, look.

1001
01:35:15,360 --> 01:35:17,590
Undo it now.

1002
01:35:26,440 --> 01:35:28,396
Cybèle.

1003
01:35:36,360 --> 01:35:38,112
Do you like it?

1004
01:35:42,280 --> 01:35:43,508
Cybèle.

1005
01:35:43,720 --> 01:35:47,269
It's your name, your real name!

1006
01:35:47,720 --> 01:35:49,472
It's lovely.

1007
01:35:49,680 --> 01:35:52,194
<i>It sounds like si belle.
"So lovely!"</i>

1008
01:35:52,800 --> 01:35:56,031
It's my name. It's me.

1009
01:35:56,440 --> 01:35:58,829
It was the name of a goddess.

1010
01:35:59,320 --> 01:36:03,199
The goddess of trees and earth.
So I was told.

1011
01:36:03,640 --> 01:36:06,393
It's a very ancient name, you know.

1012
01:36:07,040 --> 01:36:10,237
- What's the matter?
- Nothing...

1013
01:36:10,600 --> 01:36:12,431
...but later on...

1014
01:36:12,640 --> 01:36:15,200
...I'll have a surprise for you too.

1015
01:36:35,640 --> 01:36:39,633
- I thought you were never coming!
- You've seen the traffic jams.

1016
01:36:42,200 --> 01:36:44,475
And anyway,
I looked in to warn the police.

1017
01:36:44,680 --> 01:36:46,318
We're going to your place now,
I gave your telephone number.

1018
01:36:46,520 --> 01:36:47,714
- What did you do?
- It was the only thing to do.

1019
01:36:47,920 --> 01:36:50,115
I phoned the school first.
He had already been to fetch the child.

1020
01:36:50,320 --> 01:36:51,799
So I went to see the cops.

1021
01:36:52,000 --> 01:36:55,595
I shouldn't have called you.
It's my fault. You don't understand.

1022
01:36:55,800 --> 01:36:58,758
I saw them last Sunday.
They were like two happy children.

1023
01:36:58,960 --> 01:37:00,632
And you, you've gone
and denounced Pierre like a criminal.

1024
01:37:00,840 --> 01:37:02,193
It's possible, but we haven't
the right to take such a risk.

1025
01:37:02,400 --> 01:37:04,118
But what risk?
What are you thinking?

1026
01:37:04,320 --> 01:37:05,469
That he's going to kill her,
that he's going to rape her?

1027
01:37:05,680 --> 01:37:06,795
Pierre is sick,
one can expect the worst.

1028
01:37:07,000 --> 01:37:09,719
It's you who are sick -
you and Carlos' wife.

1029
01:37:09,920 --> 01:37:12,195
All of you
who call yourselves normal!

1030
01:37:12,600 --> 01:37:14,875
When you see somebody being happy
outside of your conventions...

1031
01:37:15,080 --> 01:37:17,071
...then he is not normal
and you reject him. Why?

1032
01:37:17,280 --> 01:37:19,714
Does sincerity embarrass you?

1033
01:37:20,000 --> 01:37:21,956
Even I was getting ideas.

1034
01:37:22,440 --> 01:37:24,590
Right. Listen, we're not going
to start getting sentimental.

1035
01:37:24,800 --> 01:37:26,631
To me, it's simple.
Pierre is in a violent phase.

1036
01:37:26,840 --> 01:37:29,115
Lf, in his subconscious he believes
he killed a little girl before...

1037
01:37:29,320 --> 01:37:31,038
It's you who told me so.

1038
01:37:31,520 --> 01:37:32,839
If he believes
he escaped punishment...

1039
01:37:33,040 --> 01:37:35,508
...he could easily end by killing
another in order to be punished.

1040
01:37:35,720 --> 01:37:38,393
Just to free himself
of his obsession.

1041
01:37:38,600 --> 01:37:39,874
When the human brain
is deranged, one must...

1042
01:37:40,080 --> 01:37:41,229
Oh, yes, one must,
one must, Bernard.

1043
01:37:41,440 --> 01:37:43,749
You may have a lot of sense,
but no intuition.

1044
01:37:43,960 --> 01:37:46,076
What must be done is to stop
the police from interfering in this.

1045
01:37:46,280 --> 01:37:48,840
Pierre would never get over it.
You're going to phone them.

1046
01:37:49,040 --> 01:37:50,951
Tell them anything,
that it was a joke...

1047
01:37:51,160 --> 01:37:54,152
In any case, it's too late,
the nuns have lodged a complaint.

1048
01:38:49,280 --> 01:38:50,872
The vertigo.

1049
01:38:51,400 --> 01:38:53,868
I haven't vertigo anymore!

1050
01:39:44,520 --> 01:39:46,397
<i>- Hello?
- Hello, Pierre?</i>

1051
01:39:46,600 --> 01:39:48,033
No. Who is speaking?

1052
01:39:48,240 --> 01:39:49,832
<i>Carlos.</i>

1053
01:39:50,400 --> 01:39:52,152
<i>Isn't Madeleine there?</i>

1054
01:39:53,320 --> 01:39:57,438
<i>- Hello? Carlos?
- Well, what's happening?</i>

1055
01:39:58,680 --> 01:40:01,194
It was Bernard who answered you.

1056
01:40:01,800 --> 01:40:03,597
We're waiting.

1057
01:40:04,280 --> 01:40:06,271
Bernard has called in the police.

1058
01:40:06,480 --> 01:40:08,710
<i>The police! What for? You're crazy!</i>

1059
01:40:08,920 --> 01:40:11,354
<i>What have you done?
Do you realise it?!</i>

1060
01:40:18,240 --> 01:40:19,912
Listen to me, Madeleine,
for your own sake.

1061
01:40:20,120 --> 01:40:22,395
This is no time for sentiment.

1062
01:40:22,840 --> 01:40:25,877
You don't want the phone to be busy
just when they call to let us know.

1063
01:40:44,440 --> 01:40:46,078
<i>Hello?</i>

1064
01:40:46,480 --> 01:40:48,710
<i>Madeleine? We were cut off.</i>

1065
01:40:48,920 --> 01:40:51,559
Yes. I hit it with my elbow.

1066
01:40:51,760 --> 01:40:54,274
<i>I see. I don't know what can be done
now, but things mustn't stay lik e this.</i>

1067
01:40:54,480 --> 01:40:56,391
<i>Wait for me, I'm on my way.</i>

1068
01:41:49,560 --> 01:41:52,313
Hello? Yes, it's me.

1069
01:41:53,000 --> 01:41:54,877
Ah, so they've been found?

1070
01:41:55,520 --> 01:41:57,351
What? You have killed him?

1071
01:42:51,720 --> 01:42:53,915
You can call it a real miracle!

1072
01:42:54,120 --> 01:42:56,395
Two moments later
and we would have been too late.

1073
01:42:56,600 --> 01:42:58,830
He had a dagger in his hand
and was slowly approaching the girl...

1074
01:42:59,080 --> 01:43:00,718
...who was asleep.

1075
01:43:53,040 --> 01:43:54,917
What are you called?

1076
01:43:57,640 --> 01:43:59,676
What is your name?

1077
01:44:10,360 --> 01:44:12,476
I have no name anymore.

1078
01:44:13,080 --> 01:44:16,755
I have no name anymore.
I am nobody now!

1079
01:44:16,960 --> 01:44:18,871
Nothing!

